snippet.textDisplay: The song has a story ' A story of Haji Kasam Tari Vijali' by Gunvant Acharya....It's a beautiful and tragic folktale from Saurashtra region of Gujarat....Haji Kasam was an adventurous Khalasi a seafarer who was destined to be a successful businessman (who becomes a successful traderer in Africa) and later on his fate takes his life...This tale is also attached to a ship called 'Vijali'  which got sink in the waves of Arabian sea....identically it's story is more tragic than Titanic... Salute to the community of Adventurous Seafarers of Gujarat....This song also has a spiritual power where the lyricist is also talking about the inner quest of human being in search of Almighty....The contrasting perplexity and smell of simplicity and curiosity everything defines the character of a Seafarer....what a tribute ❤❤

snippet.textDisplay:
I was here just for Achint- he is really underrated though after his quite popular compositions like from Scam 1992 title track, monica oh my darling album, after those albums really looking some hope from artists like him, composers like him will do good music HOPEFULLY, also like aditya and whole team.
BUT, there are some things that as an audience will like to suggest seriously to @CokeStudioBharat:
1) please have more patience,more thehraav in the COMPOSITION, musicality of the songs being made in future, BECAUSE THAT IS FELT MISSING , which we too really lacking that in today's Indian music, be it some casual music video to film music to such platform's music(ITS FELT THAT A SONG IS MADE BECAUSE IT HS TO BE MADE THATS WHY, rather than the love, patience,emotions involved in the process, and ONLY FOR NEW GENERATIONS, and nothing for the older generations)- It doesnt have to be ALWAYS relatable to the youth but FOR ALL.Cater to all- please dont try to follow but learn from a lot of good content quality nation's platforms' like Coke studio Pakistan, bangladesh too, but create your own new LEGACY OF TRUE TALENT, ART(dont see it as some content)
2) PLEASE REVIVE THE RICHNESS, HARMONIES, MELODIES, GOOD LYRICS,SOUND PRODUCTION WITH GOOD MUSICAL ARRANGEMENTS IN INDIAN SONGS WHICH(most importantly) WILL NOT BE FOR SOME "VIBE", OR "TRENDY", but will last for decades type. 
3) Make the songs little longer than this (like some around 6-7min as per requirement), which will include space for traditional harkats, sargams, rags/raginis for the song's composition(we are missing the indian musicality , its melodies, soul sounds drastically)
FOR ALL THESE TO HAPPEN- please call upon our legendary singers/composers/lyricist if required like Faiz anwar,sandesh shandilya, sonu nigam, harshdeep kaur,Jatin-lalit,Ismail darbar, monty sharma, shaan, mohit chauhan, etc.

આદિત્ય ગઢવી ...આપ એક ઉમદા ગાયક છો એમાં કોઈ શંકા જ નથી...ને આટલું સરસ કંપોઝ કર્યું છે ખરેખર અભિનંદનને પાત્ર છે...
પણ ભૈલા તમે ગઢવી, ચારણી સાહિત્યના ઈતિહાસ ને વારસામાં મેળવ્યા છે ... એને અંગ્રેજી સંગીત નો તડકો આપી ને કંઈક નવું કરવાની આપની ઈચ્છા સારી જ હતી પ્રસિદ્ધ પણ થશે પણ આપણી વાણી નો,ભાષા અને સાહિત્ય અને આપણા સંગીત ના ઈતિહાસ નું ગૌરવ ઘટે નહીં.. તમે દેશ વિદેશના સંગીત ને ભલે અનુસરો પણ આપણા દુહા છંદ,છપાકરા છોડતા નહી 🙏🙏
